The [Bitnami MediaWiki image](https://github.com/bitnami/bitnami-docker-mediawiki) stores the MediaWiki data and configurations at the */bitnami/mediawiki* path of the container.

Persistent Volume Claims are used to keep the data across deployments. This is known to work in GCE, AWS, and minikube. See the [Parameters section](https://github.com/bitnami/charts/tree/master/bitnami/mediawiki#parameters) to configure the PVC or to disable persistence.
